<h1>Object</h1>
<ol>
  <li>JavaScript is object based programming system.</li>

<li>An Object in javascript comprises of set of properties and methods.</li>
  <li>We can create an instance for JavaScript object in order to access its members.</li>
  <li>The members of object are invoked by using "dot" operator.</li>
  <li>The properties are defined with a value and methods are defined with function.</li>
 <li>
  <details>
    <summary>
      JavaScript object type encapsulates all the members in "{}".
    </summary>
    <pre>
      Syntax: var object = {Property: Value,Method:function(){}};
      object.Property;
      object.Method();
    </pre>
  </details>
  </li>

</ol>

<details>
  <summary>
    <font size="3" style="font-weight: bold">Object Example</font>
  </summary>
  <div>

    <form>
      <input type="button" value="Show Product Details" onclick="ShowClick();" style="background-color: cadetblue;color: white">
      <input type="button" id="hide" value="Hide Product Details" onclick="HideClick();" style="background-color: cadetblue;color: white;display: none"><br><br>
      <table id="details" width="561" border="1" style="display: none;text-align: center" bgcolor="white">
        <tr>
          <td><img id="pic" width="200" height="200"></td>

          <td>

            <table frame="box" rules="all" align="center" width="350" style="text-align: center" bgcolor="white">
              <tr>
                <td>Product id</td>
                <td id="prodId"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Product Name</td>
                <td id="prodName"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Product Price</td>
                <td id="prodPrice"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Stock</td>
                <td id="IsInstock"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Shipped To</td>
                <td id="shipped"></td>
              </tr>
            </table>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </form>
  </div>
</details>

